  (text "CONNECTIVITY NOTES:\n\nAll Qwiic and Grove signals originate from the STM32U585 (UNO Q MCU).\nThe ESP32-S3 does NOT drive these connectors.\n\nQWIIC:\n  Standard SparkFun/Adafruit Qwiic spec: 3.3V, I2C, 100/400kHz\n  4.7kΩ pullups R5/R6 on SDA/SCL to +3V3\n  Daisy-chain: J8 and J9 are electrically parallel\n  Cable polarity: GND=black, 3V3=red, SDA=blue, SCL=yellow\n\nGROVE:\n  J10 I2C:    SIG1=SDA, SIG2=SCL (from STM32U585)\n  J11 UART:   SIG1=TX,  SIG2=RX  (STM32U585 UART)\n  J12 SPI:    SIG1=MOSI,SIG2=SCK (STM32U585 SPI, CS via JDIGITAL)\n  J13 Digital:SIG1=GPIO,SIG2=GPIO (STM32U585 GPIO)\n  J14 Analog: SIG1=ADC0,SIG2=ADC1 (STM32U585 ADC)\n  All Grove signals: 3.3V max. Do not connect 5V Grove sensors directly."
    (at 30 75 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top)))
